# ── Optional: Google Places (richer data, full mall/indoor coverage) ──────────
# Template only — copy to ".env.local" and put your real key there (Next.js reads
# .env.local, NOT this file). .env.local is git-ignored; never commit a real key.
#
# Without a key the app uses free OpenStreetMap automatically. With a key, each
# search tries Google first and AUTO-FALLS BACK to OSM on any failure (quota /
# billing off / API disabled / network) — so the site never goes down.
#
# Setup:
#   1. console.cloud.google.com → create a project.
#   2. Enable "Places API (New)" — NOT the legacy "Places API"; they're separate.
#   3. APIs & Services → Credentials → create an API key. Restrict it to the
#      "Places API (New)" (Application restrictions can stay "None" since the key
#      is only used server-side, never sent to the browser).
#   4. Staying free: only the cheap "Nearby Search Pro" SKU is requested
#      (~5,000 calls/MONTH free; resets on the 1st, not daily). The New Places
#      API per-day quota is "Unlimited / not adjustable", so you can't set a hard
#      request cap — instead stay on the Free Trial credit (Google won't charge
#      your card; it pauses when credit/90 days run out) and add a low budget
#      alert in Billing → Budgets & alerts. Don't click "Activate" unless you
#      want pay-as-you-go billing.
#
# GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=your-key-here
